The key insight is that `IsTotalTimeDerivative` says there exists F such that for all r, v, t:
δL v = fderiv ℝ F (r, t) (v, 1)

Since the left side is independent of r and t, the right side must also be independent of r and t. This means fderiv ℝ F (r, t) (v, 1) is constant in r and t.

For a differentiable F, fderiv ℝ F (r, t) (v, 1) is linear in (v, 1). The part linear in v gives us our inner product with some vector g.

